G-SEL-CANON — margin-gated query canonicalization (2026-07-02) — PARKED (honest negative)
=========================================================================================
HYPOTHESIS (G-SEL-RERANK-61 follow-on): on an ambiguous L5 margin (eps=0.015), one generative
micro-step resolves the query's periphrasis to a PROPER NAME ("boot-shaped Mediterranean
country" -> "Italy"); the name appears verbatim in exactly the right fact, so a conservative
strictly-greater salient-overlap switch over the L5 top-5 fixes the cross-picks without the
judge's slot-picking unreliability.

MECHANICS BUILT (kept, default-off SP_RECALL_L5_CANON): micro-forward with suppress-token
masking (the <image|> raw-argmax spam relearned+fixed in run-1, same cure as the judge verify
path), first-line parse, recall::canon_overlap (morphology-tolerant salient overlap),
strictly-greater switch rule, fail-open.

THREE PROMPT FRAMINGS, ONE FAILURE MODE — the 12B ANSWERS instead of resolving:
  run-2 "rewrite with proper names":            swaps one periphrasis for another
                                                ("island nation east of Korea"), or answers
                                                ("Alexander Graham Bell is credited with...")
  run-3 "rewrite; one-shot exemplar; do not answer":
                                                answers anyway ("Alexander Graham Bell.",
                                                "...is Jupiter.")
  run-4 "name the DESCRIBED subject, not the answer; exemplar":
                                                still answers ("Jupiter.", "Alexander Graham
                                                Bell.", "South Korean Won.") — AND the
                                                parametric answer token then matched a WRONG
                                                fact: largest_planet switched to fct_023
                                                (red_planet, text contains "Jupiter") = a NEW
                                                break. Run killed; mechanism conclusive.

VERDICT: **PARKED.** At temp-0 in a bare micro-prompt, this instruct 12B's dominant behavior
on a periphrasis question is to ANSWER it (parametrically), not to name/rewrite the subject —
across all three framings. Worse, the parametric answer token systematically collides with
WRONG facts (the corpus plants counterfacts), so the overlap switch converts model priors into
selection errors. Query canonicalization joins judge-rerank in the drawer; the deterministic
switch machinery + suppress-masked micro-forward remain in the tree (default-off) for reuse.

SELECTOR CAMPAIGN CLOSE (the honest ledger):
  margin gate            CONVICTED (G-L5-MARGIN-CALIB: SNE margins 0.0003-0.0007)
  fact-text key2         INERT (G-SEL-OFFLINE)
  raw-query Jaccard fusion INERT (G-SEL-OFFLINE)
  judge top-3 rerank     PARKED (G-SEL-RERANK-61: +5/-4, fails no-regression)
  query canonicalization PARKED (this gate: model answers instead of resolving)
The deployed selector stays L5-cosine top-1 = 54/61 (88.5%) on this deliberately-adversarial
periphrasis corpus; the composition (G-ONECONFIG-LIVE) remains GREEN with 0 leaks. Residual
ideas (design-level, unbuilt): multi-phrasing ep.l5 keys accumulated per episode over live
usage (CANNOT be gated on this corpus — adding its paras as keys = training on the test set);
a stronger dedicated resolver (e.g. the qwen coder via Telepathy delegate) at higher cost.
DIMINISHING RETURNS DECLARED: the audit plan's bigger items (artifact-hole #2, N1 exact
prefill GEMM, SWARM multi-host) outrank further selector work.

